+      "content": "The Week 5 challenge asks for a v2. Your teammate has read the build and told you what broke. The move is iteration. The trap is regeneration: a fresh prompt, a fresh draft, no record of what you decided to change. Two prompts do the work.\n\nPrompt one is the diff. Open a new chat. Paste your v1 and the teammate notes. Ask: \"Compare this output to the feedback. Produce a three-column changelist: KEEP (what worked and why), FIX (what needs revision and what specifically to change), CUT (what should be removed and why). Be concrete on the FIX column: name the sentence or section.\" The prompt does no rewriting. It produces a list you can scan in a minute and decide on.\n\nPrompt two is the rewrite. In the same chat: \"Apply only the FIX items to produce a v2. Leave the KEEP sections untouched. Show me what changed and why.\" The constraint is what keeps the v2 honest. Without it, the model rewrites everything and your iteration loop collapses into a regenerate loop.\n\nThe split exposes your judgment. The teammate told you what broke. The first prompt makes the model show you what to do about it. You decide the FIX list before any new prose gets written. That is the move Week 5 asks for: cut what's thin, sharpen what's vague, name the human checkpoint that stays. The capstone seed lives in the FIX column you signed off on. The v2 chat is downstream of that decision.",
+      "date": "2026-05-05",
